# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: LifeInRahayal | Scene: SarahAndNick1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke to the earliest beams of light from the dawn."
    new "Sarah woke to the earliest beams of light from the dawn."

    old "Sheltered, warmed by the fire and waking to the gentle and ethereal light of the Hyral mountains splintering on the fog, Sarah imagined herself dreaming."
    new "Sheltered, warmed by the fire and waking to the gentle and ethereal light of the Hyral mountains splintering on the fog, Sarah imagined herself dreaming."

    old "The light seemed to diffuse, turning beams into almost a mist of sun."
    new "The light seemed to diffuse, turning beams into almost a mist of sun."

    old "Perhaps she had died, she thought, and for her troubled life the gods had seen fit to reward her."
    new "Perhaps she had died, she thought, and for her troubled life the gods had seen fit to reward her."

    old "But as she drew in the could mountain air, she was reminded that she was still on the mortal plan."
    new "But as she drew in the could mountain air, she was reminded that she was still on the mortal plan."

    old "Opposite of her, she could see Nick was still sleeping. The rising and falling of his chest telling her he had, thankfully, not died in his sleep during the night."
    new "Opposite of her, she could see Nick was still sleeping. The rising and falling of his chest telling her he had, thankfully, not died in his sleep during the night."

    old "As she put her hands against the cave floor, she felt the cold stones press against her palms."
    new "As she put her hands against the cave floor, she felt the cold stones press against her palms."

    old "It was a strange kind of coldness, the kind that only existed in places that never knew anything other than cold."
    new "It was a strange kind of coldness, the kind that only existed in places that never knew anything other than cold."

    old "Outside, the landscape was still covered in snow."
    new "Outside, the landscape was still covered in snow."

    old "What little Sarah knew of this place, she knew that the snow here was permanent. No passing of the seasons affected it."
    new "What little Sarah knew of this place, she knew that the snow here was permanent. No passing of the seasons affected it."

    old "As she looked towards Nick and herself, and made an account of what little they had, she began to worry."
    new "As she looked towards Nick and herself, and made an account of what little they had, she began to worry."

    old "Their clothes were a poor fit for the cold."
    new "Their clothes were a poor fit for the cold."

    old "The cave and the campfire went a long way in keeping them warm, but they had no food. They couldn't stay in the cave for long or they would starve."
    new "The cave and the campfire went a long way in keeping them warm, but they had no food. They couldn't stay in the cave for long or they would starve."

    old "They would have to set out soon."
    new "They would have to set out soon."

    old "But the nearest human settlement was hundreds of miles by coast."
    new "But the nearest human settlement was hundreds of miles by coast."

    old "Worse still, they could not follow the coastline. The jagged rocks and stabbing mountains that rose up towards the heavens made a natural barrier against the ocean."
    new "Worse still, they could not follow the coastline. The jagged rocks and stabbing mountains that rose up towards the heavens made a natural barrier against the ocean."

    old "This small bay was a rare exception in an otherwise inhospitable land."
    new "This small bay was a rare exception in an otherwise inhospitable land."

    old "Sarah tried to conceive of a plan."
    new "Sarah tried to conceive of a plan."

    old "They would have to travel inwards, up through the Hyral mountains. A tough journey, even when prepared. And they were not prepared."
    new "They would have to travel inwards, up through the Hyral mountains. A tough journey, even when prepared. And they were not prepared."

    old "An easy mistake and they would starve or freeze to death. Possibly both."
    new "An easy mistake and they would starve or freeze to death. Possibly both."

    old "All this was enough to trouble Sarah, had she not also known what the Hyral mountains were most famous for."
    new "All this was enough to trouble Sarah, had she not also known what the Hyral mountains were most famous for."

    old "The homeland of the orcs and goblins."
    new "The homeland of the orcs and goblins."

    old "Once a formidable race that had ruled over large swathes of land, over time they had been driven back by the advance of human civilization."
    new "Once a formidable race that had ruled over large swathes of land, over time they had been driven back by the advance of human civilization."

    old "The orcs made impressive warriors, but they did not have the organization to field large armies the way humans did."
    new "The orcs made impressive warriors, but they did not have the organization to field large armies the way humans did."

    old "Their smaller warbands were excellent for raiding, but against the armies of humanity, and especially the Mythran empire, they stood no chance."
    new "Their smaller warbands were excellent for raiding, but against the armies of humanity, and especially the Mythran empire, they stood no chance."

    old "The orcs were pushed back until eventually only their ancestral homeland remained. The Hyral mountains."
    new "The orcs were pushed back until eventually only their ancestral homeland remained. The Hyral mountains."

    old "These mountains, dangerous and inhospitable, could not support large armies in the way the open plains could."
    new "These mountains, dangerous and inhospitable, could not support large armies in the way the open plains could."

    old "In this place, the orcs could play to their advantages."
    new "In this place, the orcs could play to their advantages."

    old "But rather than settle the fight, humanity had simply considered it finished."
    new "But rather than settle the fight, humanity had simply considered it finished."

    old "The orcs were a small threat, worth little more than the occasional consideration."
    new "The orcs were a small threat, worth little more than the occasional consideration."

    old "Let them have the mountains."
    new "Let them have the mountains."

    old "And so the orcs, forgotten and ignored, did what all irrelevant peoples did. They obsessed over the trivial and small things of life."
    new "And so the orcs, forgotten and ignored, did what all irrelevant peoples did. They obsessed over the trivial and small things of life."

    old "They fought among each other. They carried out the occasional raid when they dared."
    new "They fought among each other. They carried out the occasional raid when they dared."

    old "Where once they had ruled empires, now they squabbled over who might hold claim over a pretty farm girl that was captured in some insignificant raid on a frontier town."
    new "Where once they had ruled empires, now they squabbled over who might hold claim over a pretty farm girl that was captured in some insignificant raid on a frontier town."

    old "Meanwhile, the Mythran empire was not in a mood to waste its legions to rescue poor farmers."
    new "Meanwhile, the Mythran empire was not in a mood to waste its legions to rescue poor farmers."

    old "This was the peace that had settled on the lands between humans and orcs."
    new "This was the peace that had settled on the lands between humans and orcs."

    old "A brutal peace, where as often, the weakest and poorest were made to pay the price."
    new "A brutal peace, where as often, the weakest and poorest were made to pay the price."

    old "Sarah shuddered as she put all of the threats together."
    new "Sarah shuddered as she put all of the threats together."

    old "She had no illusions what would happen if she fell into the hands of an orc warband."
    new "She had no illusions what would happen if she fell into the hands of an orc warband."

    old "She sighed, how had she allowed herself to fall into this situation."
    new "She sighed, how had she allowed herself to fall into this situation."

    old "Looking across the cave, she saw Nick, still sleeping."
    new "Looking across the cave, she saw Nick, still sleeping."

    old "That was it. Her one ally. Her one resource."
    new "That was it. Her one ally. Her one resource."

    old "He could work a ship and looked strong enough, but would he be strong enough to fight off an orc attack?."
    new "He could work a ship and looked strong enough, but would he be strong enough to fight off an orc attack?."

    old "Slowly, she saw him begin to stir."
    new "Slowly, she saw him begin to stir."

    old "His voice was soft. Likely still weakened by the frigid water."
    new "His voice was soft. Likely still weakened by the frigid water."

    old "Hey. Did you get any good sleep?"
    new "Hey. Did you get any good sleep?"

    old "He slightly nodded."
    new "He slightly nodded."

    old "I think I did."
    new "I think I did."

    old "She saw him look outside of the cave."
    new "She saw him look outside of the cave."

    old "We're so screwed..."
    new "We're so screwed..."

    old "Don't say that. We'll need to keep our hopes of if we want any chance of getting out of here."
    new "Don't say that. We'll need to keep our hopes of if we want any chance of getting out of here."

    old "He looked back at her."
    new "He looked back at her."

    old "Getting out of here? We're in the middle of the Hyral mountains. Better if we'd have just drowned."
    new "Getting out of here? We're in the middle of the Hyral mountains. Better if we'd have just drowned."

    old "Sarah grew frustrated."
    new "Sarah grew frustrated."

    old "Well, if you want, go ahead and dive in then. I'm going to try and get out of here, alive."
    new "Well, if you want, go ahead and dive in then. I'm going to try and get out of here, alive."

    old "She saw him lower his head."
    new "She saw him lower his head."

    old "Sorry, I just thought...our odds aren't exactly good."
    new "Sorry, I just thought...our odds aren't exactly good."

    old "Trust me, I know that."
    new "Trust me, I know that."

    old "Sarah spoke with Nick, going through their options."
    new "Sarah spoke with Nick, going through their options."

    old "In the end, each understood that no matter what, there was one reality they could not ignore."
    new "In the end, each understood that no matter what, there was one reality they could not ignore."

    old "There was no food here, so they could not stay. The longer they did, the worse their food situation would get."
    new "There was no food here, so they could not stay. The longer they did, the worse their food situation would get."

    old "Right, so we agree? We'll need to leave. Today."
    new "Right, so we agree? We'll need to leave. Today."

    old "She could see the fear on his face."
    new "She could see the fear on his face."

    old "He might have had a tough life growing up, but deep down he was still a city boy, unfamiliar with these harsh lands."
    new "He might have had a tough life growing up, but deep down he was still a city boy, unfamiliar with these harsh lands."

    old "For a brief moment, Sarah thought that Belmont would have known what to do. He would have taken charge."
    new "For a brief moment, Sarah thought that Belmont would have known what to do. He would have taken charge."

    old "Sarah shook her head. She had made her choice, and now this was it."
    new "Sarah shook her head. She had made her choice, and now this was it."

    old "She'd have to take the lead, even though she was no more prepared for it than Nick."
    new "She'd have to take the lead, even though she was no more prepared for it than Nick."

    old "Let's get packing."
    new "Let's get packing."

    old "Together, they started working, packing what little they had. Fixing their clothes as best they could against the cold."
    new "Together, they started working, packing what little they had. Fixing their clothes as best they could against the cold."

    old "Before long, they were finished and stood near the entrance of the cave."
    new "Before long, they were finished and stood near the entrance of the cave."

    old "Looking out, Sarah saw the endless fields of snow before her. The looming mountains."
    new "Looking out, Sarah saw the endless fields of snow before her. The looming mountains."

    old "She was afraid."
    new "She was afraid."

    old "She knew she could not stay here, but she equally feared leaving the safety of the cave."
    new "She knew she could not stay here, but she equally feared leaving the safety of the cave."

    old "Despite all her fears, Sarah began her journey same as any other, with a single step."
    new "Despite all her fears, Sarah began her journey same as any other, with a single step."

    old "Instantly, the cold advanced on them."
    new "Instantly, the cold advanced on them."

    old "Sarah forced herself to keep to a steady march as she plowed through the thick layer of snow."
    new "Sarah forced herself to keep to a steady march as she plowed through the thick layer of snow."

    old "It wasn't long before the cave was far behind them and the whole world seemed to be made out of snow."
    new "It wasn't long before the cave was far behind them and the whole world seemed to be made out of snow."

    old "There was so much of it, a pure white, that it at times disoriented her."
    new "There was so much of it, a pure white, that it at times disoriented her."

    old "With each passing step, the brutal winds of the Hyral Mountains grew harsher and harsher, as if warning them to turn back."
    new "With each passing step, the brutal winds of the Hyral Mountains grew harsher and harsher, as if warning them to turn back."

    old "This was not a land made for people."
    new "This was not a land made for people."

    old "Only the brutish orcs could survive in a place so hostile to life."
    new "Only the brutish orcs could survive in a place so hostile to life."

    old "As the winds grew in intensity, they ripped and tore at both Sarah and Nick's cloak."
    new "As the winds grew in intensity, they ripped and tore at both Sarah and Nick's cloak."

    old "Sarah let slip the garment, only for a moment, and a cold that cut deep into her skin rushed in."
    new "Sarah let slip the garment, only for a moment, and a cold that cut deep into her skin rushed in."

    old "Growing in intensity by each passing moment, the wind began to howl."
    new "Growing in intensity by each passing moment, the wind began to howl."

    old "A shrieking sound bombarded their ears, as the hardened snow pelted at their faces like rocks."
    new "A shrieking sound bombarded their ears, as the hardened snow pelted at their faces like rocks."

    old "And the cold sank deeper and deeper through their fabrics, and skin, taking rest deep in their bones."
    new "And the cold sank deeper and deeper through their fabrics, and skin, taking rest deep in their bones."

    old "Step by step, Sarah kept pushing forward, because to stop was certain death."
    new "Step by step, Sarah kept pushing forward, because to stop was certain death."

    old "Still, despite the best of her hopes, she began to fear for the worst."
    new "Still, despite the best of her hopes, she began to fear for the worst."

    old "Neither of them had much experience surviving out in the wild."
    new "Neither of them had much experience surviving out in the wild."

    old "And these mountains could prove a test for the most tested of veterans."
    new "And these mountains could prove a test for the most tested of veterans."

    old "So for a moment, she wondered."
    new "So for a moment, she wondered."

    old "What if she had made a mistake."
    new "What if she had made a mistake."

    old "To leave the safety of the cave, to be exposed to the elements, or worse..."
    new "To leave the safety of the cave, to be exposed to the elements, or worse..."

    old "Her own mortality was suddenly a very conscious fact."
    new "Her own mortality was suddenly a very conscious fact."

    old "Sarah shook her head and forced herself to keep moving."
    new "Sarah shook her head and forced herself to keep moving."

    old "No, horrible as this was, the cave meant accepting a slow death."
    new "No, horrible as this was, the cave meant accepting a slow death."

    old "Despite the torture of the howling blizzard, at least, they might live."
    new "Despite the torture of the howling blizzard, at least, they might live."

    old "They pressed on, neither speaking, not until the torment becam too much and their exhaustion broke them."
    new "They pressed on, neither speaking, not until the torment becam too much and their exhaustion broke them."

    old "I can't feel my feet...my hands...my...anything..."
    new "I can't feel my feet...my hands...my...anything..."

    old "His voice was soft, almost hard to hear over they gyre."
    new "His voice was soft, almost hard to hear over they gyre."

    old "Just a bit more."
    new "Just a bit more."

    old "I think...I see a spot up that hill where we can rest."
    new "I think...I see a spot up that hill where we can rest."

    old "Nick walked up beside her."
    new "Nick walked up beside her."

    old "Finally..."
    new "Finally..."

    old "Some rest...a fire..."
    new "Some rest...a fire..."

    old "The cold was overpowering. Her limbs trembled."
    new "The cold was overpowering. Her limbs trembled."

    old "She wanted nothing more than heat...but a fire was a risk."
    new "She wanted nothing more than heat...but a fire was a risk."

    old "Out here, they would stand out in the dark. And who knew what lurked in the dark."
    new "Out here, they would stand out in the dark. And who knew what lurked in the dark."

    old "Then again, she doubted anyone but them would be crazy enough to endure this blizzard."
    new "Then again, she doubted anyone but them would be crazy enough to endure this blizzard."

    old "And she feared the cold almost as much as any creature or beast."
    new "And she feared the cold almost as much as any creature or beast."

    old "What if they collapsed from exhaustion? Only to die in their sleep from the exposure to the cold?"
    new "What if they collapsed from exhaustion? Only to die in their sleep from the exposure to the cold?"

    old "Sarah wasn't sure what the best option was."
    new "Sarah wasn't sure what the best option was."

    old "Make a fire"
    new "Make a fire"

    old "Hug together for warmth"
    new "Hug together for warmth"

